HEADWORD: Laodicean
<hw>La*od`i*ce"an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining
to <etsep>Laodicea</etsep>, a city in Phrygia Major; like the Christians
of Laodicea; lukewarm in religion.</def> <rj><au>Rev. iii.
14-16.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
